name: 'Umbrellas Underground' Fine Art Print
description:
Ever left your umbrella on the tube!?

80000 umbrellas are left on the London Underground every year. 
This piece graphically illustrates their journeys along the familiar coloured tracking of the tube lines, leading to the numbers of umbrellas left on each tube line every year.

These figures were worked out pro rata using data from TFL representing the number of passengers on each line per year and the average number of umbrellas collected in lost property per year.


High quality Giclee Fine Art Print on heavyweight etching board -  Hahnemuhle German Etching (310gsm), available as A3 or A2. Unframed.
